By: Rand Fishkin March 6, 2006 HighRankings Conference in San Francisco SEO Events The author's views are entirely their own (excluding the unlikely event of hypnosis) and may not always reflect the views of Moz. The "Events" category on SEOmoz has been getting all the entries lately, but there's one more to add to the list. Jill Whalen and the HighRankings crew are running their Search Engine Marketing Seminar in Walnut Creek, CA (just outside San Francisco) at the end of March. Details are below:The High Rankings Search Engine Marketing SeminarThursday March 30 and Friday March 31, 2006The Holiday Inn Walnut Creek, CARegistration before March 15th is $1195.After March 15th, it is $1395See the agenda and registration details and, if you're feeling frisky (or in need of some good eyeballs), there's sponsorship opportunities too. Somehow I managed to miss Jill while I was in NYC, so I'll have to try to meet up with her in Toronto or elsewhere. I've been a recent re-converted fan of the forum, so it's only fair that I give here some props. Copied! Back to Top
